Yeliztli — Third-Party Data Attribution
============================================

This product redistributes data derived from the following sources. It is the
companion to the MIT LICENSE (which covers Yeliztli's own source code).

gnomAD (Genome Aggregation Database)
------------------------------------
Source:   https://gnomad.broadinstitute.org/
License:  CC0 1.0 (public domain dedication) — primary allele-frequency data.
Scope:    Allele frequencies and homozygous counts only (table `gnomad_af`).
          No SpliceAI, CADD, REVEL, SIFT, PolyPhen, or any CC-BY-NC /
          academic-license-restricted predictor columns are included.
Version:  gnomAD v2.1.1 (GRCh37 exomes).
Citation: Karczewski, K.J., Francioli, L.C., Tiao, G. et al.
          "The mutational constraint spectrum quantified from variation in
          141,456 humans." Nature 581, 434–443 (2020).
          doi:10.1038/s41586-020-2308-7

"gnomAD" and "Broad Institute" are trademarks of their respective owners and
are used here solely for source attribution. Yeliztli is an independent
project and is not affiliated with or endorsed by the Broad Institute.

ClinGen (Clinical Genome Resource) — Gene-Disease Validity
----------------------------------------------------------
Source:   https://search.clinicalgenome.org/kb/gene-validity
License:  CC0 1.0 (public domain dedication). ClinGen requests attribution and
          the date accessed even though CC0 imposes no legal requirement; we
          honor that request here.
Scope:    Gene-disease validity classifications (Definitive / Strong / Moderate /
          Limited / Disputed / Refuted / No Known Disease Relationship) only,
          used as a context-only guardrail (table `clingen_gene_validity`). No
          ClinGen logo is used.
Accessed: 2026-06-11 (file build date stamped in the bundled snapshot).
Citation: Strande, N.T., Riggs, E.R., Buchanan, A.H. et al. "Evaluating the
          Clinical Validity of Gene-Disease Associations: An Evidence-Based
          Framework Developed by the Clinical Genome Resource."
          Am. J. Hum. Genet. 100(6), 895–906 (2017). doi:10.1016/j.ajhg.2017.04.015
          See clinicalgenome.org for current classifications.

"ClinGen" and "Clinical Genome Resource" are used here solely for source
attribution. Yeliztli is an independent project and is not affiliated with or
endorsed by ClinGen or the NIH.
